{
  "stem": "19055.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 249.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And hundreds and hundreds of prepared sandwiches were in there, which he gave us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he distributed to the people in front of the police and gendarmerie without any fear and wished us good luck.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we waited-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we waited, too afraid-- for afraid to-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to take over us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Anyway, they took us to the railroad station.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was the first time I encountered the new terminology, the boxcar or cattle car, that came into our lives.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they put us in cattle cars in that little town.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And a, a good number of people were out witnessing this and cheering and hollering, they're taking the Jews away.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They're taking the Jews.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Jews are leaving town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And here again, before I, I give up on all mankind and, and, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and try to remember something pleasant, a taxi arrived to the railroad station.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a Presbyterian-- or I say reformed Presbyterian minister came with his wife and baby.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They got out of the car.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They came to the boxcar where my family was with the open door.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He came quite close.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He lifted his baby, put it in the boxcar.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he said, kiss my baby before you leave.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that's again in front of the village, in front of the Nazis, in front of the gendarmerie, fearlessly.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I who lived through those times afterwards and communism, I can appreciate now far more than then.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But it gave us really courage to go in and face the life ahead.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Prior to the occupation, yes, we were still in high school, thank to the principal of the high school, whose name was Miklos Nagy-- N-A-G-Y, like Imre Nagy.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
